Lockdown Story #12 @crunchnlunge ::Well the lockdown, like any other obstacle, came as a test. In terms of training outdoors - yes, running was disrupted, had other plans too in my mind and they were all shut down. But training indoors was not too different for me. I have been training indoors for years now. Never been to a gym, never liked that gym culture in the first place. Always wanted something athletic, movement based, so opened one athletic centre in my basement only and built it over the years, and kept at it. But in the end for me in terms of personal growth this was just a different phase, not too difficult, in fact rewarding.
Inspite of the all the inconveniences that have been caused, here I am lauding the lockdown. But then thats what life is made of - tackling the disappointments, the set backs and carrying them on with you - in your mind - in your emotions and using them as a gift, as a blessing rather than a curse. Giving them a whole new, opposite meaning.

With this on going pandemic I have now started giving people virtual
sessions. What i make people do at home is literally what I have done at my home, all my life and the foundation only got stronger during this whole time. I have only gained.

*Long Post*
The word is a confusing place to be in, not only today or now or this year but all the time. 

People are running behind a lot of things that a pandemic has put a halt to... The world has been on a standstill, people losing their jobs, losing their identity, and most ironically living out of fear... 

As people, we tend to make plans that are 5 years long or 10 years long... I will be in this position or I will achieve this or that by the year 20xx. 

With the standstill at hand, most of us are lost admits the plans we made because the pandemic has shown us that it's going to have to wait. 

A world that was so involved in a rat race has now begun to move backward, giving time to things that actually mattered. A pandemic has brightened the chances of human connections. We are moving back to our primitive states. 

Like I said the world is a confusing place to be in not only today or tomorrow but all the time... With the fear of uncertainty hovering over our heads, it's about time we get our priorities set straight, our goals and ambitions set more realistically and to be humble through time. 

The confusion will not wash away even if things resolve with the pandemic as the world will present itself with confusion all over again... 

All you can do is give yourself time! The world will continue to be a mess but it's time for a change - that only you can start

You’re a wonderful tale of triumph and strength Matthew ? And from a fellow Hove’y to another...BN3 is most definitely the place to be ?

Matthew Campbell, 23, says moving to Hove in January has been ‘world changing’.
“I have a cleft palate, so I've always made myself look different. I know people are going to look at me whatever I do. Back in Devon where I’m from I’ve had stuff thrown at me down the street. Here, people are so positive. It’s incredible to live in a place where people can be free. And yet it’s hard to believe that it’s so radical - in 2020 - to be yourself. But that’s what it is and that’s why I moved here,” he said. 
Matthew works on new product launches in branding and social media for Irregular Choice, the iconic shoe and fashion brand founded in Brighton. “It has that unique quality that everyone loves.”
He says he has loved fashion since he was a child and was the costume designer for all his school plays. “I used to play with dolls to escape and then I fell in love with clothes.”
Growing up, Matthew needed 12 surgeries - the first when he was a baby and the last just two years ago. He says the most difficult was having his jaw broken and realigned which meant he couldn’t eat solid food for three months. He has also had to cope with the psychological impact of the operations.
“It’s been crazy, my face keeps changing.”
Matthew says he has always worn both men’s and women’s clothes. Several years ago, one Halloween whilst studying footwear design at Leicester University, he decided to go out in drag. He then started performing under the pseudonym Dame Deadly, dressing up as Cruella de Vil and other characters.
Matthew - who describes himself as the sparkly sheep of the family - says his brother, mother and step-dad all work for the NHS. He has been worried about them during the pandemic and has missed them. His flatmate moved home during lockdown, so he spent a lot of time alone at home, working and sewing and experimenting with clothes. Recently, when his mum was finally allowed to visit, she was so pleased to see him looking happy.
“She said I looked awake again.”
Matthew can’t imagine moving back to Devon where he says he was bullied relentlessly as a child.
“But they’re all working in Tesco now and I’m branding beautiful shoes in Brighton,” he said.

.
- Today marks 50 amazing days home every day with my best friend and our amazing daddy. Every day is our favorite day of the week now. 
- This morning HR's mom thought she was being very clever when she commented on a family group that she saw HR was up late and is probably still asleep before 7am. HR immediately replied to inform her that she had in fact been up since 6am and had done a load of laundry already, while Ouma Liefie probably hadn't been as productive. (Turned out to be only 1 of 4 loads of laundry HR went on to do).
- It was a good start to the day, not every day you can upstage your perfect mom. 
- Pieter had a good work day and the co-workers slept very late. It was a very calm and happy day.
- We also welcomed a new employee at the office, his name is Kevin A 'Sole. We are still getting to know him and will keep you updated on how it goes. 
- We're not sure if HR and Kevin's personalities will clash. He's nothing like Pieter though. He often does silly things that cause HR extra work and he laughed when HR struggled to clean the dishes with the new vegan dishwashing liquid she wanted to try out. (Simple Truth brand from Checkers - I don't recommend it. Some if their other products I love though)
.
Sincerely,
HR
.

- We will start this report with some news about the weekend. As Pieter already informed the CEO, unfortunately over the weekend while Marli was working overtime, she accidentally knocked over a glass that still had a couple sips of water in...onto the laptop.

• "Lockdown Office" Home Hub Update - Day 45 - Night Shift • 
.
- We bring you this special report for last night's night shift from 20:30 to 01:00am. Luckily some of the employees fell asleep before the time. We won't hold it against them that they didn't work the full shift. 
- The shift started with everyone excited on the couch with ice cream and a story playing in the background. Pieter doesn't usually let us stay up past our bedtime because he's the only person in the house that's not a night owl. 
- There were some interesting events during the shift. Everyone played and watched stories but as the shift went on they lost interest in their work. That's when things got interesting. 
- Co-worker Nina didn't want to be carried on HR to fall asleep in the carrier and didn't believe it was bed time when HR put her in bed. She knew we were trying to fool her and that the rest was still up and having fun without her. So I placed her in the chair to watch me do the dishes. 
- Co-worker Marli tried to negotiate with HR for more ice cream and chocolate sauce and finally said she will go play nicely if I hand over an easter egg as bribe. We don't usually allow bribes in the office but she had us between 'a rock and a hard place'. Knowing she had the power .
- Co-worker Marli kicked over Pieter's full cup of Milo onto a WHITE blanket. HR quickly cleaned up the floor and put all the Milo contaminated toys and blankets in the washing machine. 
- This was actually a blessing in disguise because Nina could then be entertained with the washing machine "TV". 
- Co-worker Marli tried to reach the small magnets HR had placed at the top of the fridge while HR had her back turned doing dishes. She exclaimed "Ohh no! I need a longer arm!" While she was on her ladder. She ran off and returned a couple minutes later with a Barbie in her hand, Barbie's arm extended to reach the magnets. 
.

During this time state borders will also remain sealed. After this, the Chief Secretary has called upon a high-level meeting on Friday to decide Lockdown and other essential arrangements.

In fact, on Thursday, 199 new cases of covid infection were reported across the state. In the view of increasing cases, a discussion with Chief Secretary Utpal Kumar Singh and Health Secretary Amit Negi late in the evening, CM expressed his concern over the increasing number of patients in the state. He said that every possible step should be taken to prevent the spread of infection & if necessary, along with sealing the state boundaries a serious step should be taken for complete lockdown of the state on Saturday and Sunday.

The facilities of the people coming here and the tourists who have booked in the hotels will also have to be taken care of. Only those people who are coming for the most essential work should be allowed in lockdown.

So today I wanted to show you a quick easy make up look that can basically be used for any occasion a day at the office, date night, even a chilled Sunday family lunch.

I also wanted to do a tutorial that allows people to create this look using the make up they have right now!

I generally like to start of with applying mascara and eyeliner which are my two favorites and I feel like I’ve set a basis for my look. I’ve been using the Essence volumn stylist mascara and the long lasting eyeliner as well. These are my staples and youll literally never catch me without these!

Next I go in with my foundation which is the L’Oral True Match in the shade Honey. Its important to find a “pliable” foundation that works with your skin. Because a lot of the foundations can end up looking cakey.

Next I went in with a little bit of the Mac Pro longwear concealer which also assists in highlighting  and illuminates the area.

For the eyeshadow I chose a wintry rusty colour and applied that to my entire eyelid. Just to add a little bit of sparkle I added a bronze glitter but only to the centre part of my eyelid.

And then we highligh?... I applied the Essence highlighter in the shade 10 Heroic to my cheek bones the tip of my nose and chin and a little of my forehead as well..

Last but not least to complete the look, some lipstick ?. I used the Wet n Wild lipstick ,in the shade Bare it all! This had definitely become my go to favorite lipstick!
